Package Logic

Class Employee

java.lang.Object
Logic.Employee
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
Direct Known Subclasses:
PersonalTrainer
public class Employee extends Object implements Serializable
Represents an employee with attributes such as ID, first name, last name, address, phone, and salary. Implements the Serializable interface for object serialization.

  • Constructor Details

    • Employee

      public Employee(String firstName, String lastName, String address, String phone, double salary)
      Constructs a new Employee object with the specified first name, last name, address, phone, and salary. The ID is assigned as the total number of employees plus one.
      Parameters:
      firstName - the first name of the employee
      lastName - the last name of the employee
      address - the address of the employee
      phone - the phone number of the employee
      salary - the salary of the employee
